    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>School of Tibetan painting that originated in the early 15th century with an artist known as Menla Töndrup. It maintained the simplicity and spaciousness of the Kadam school while placing greater emphasis on rich detail, a result of Persian influence.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Escuela de pintura tibetana que apareció a principios del siglo XV con un artista conocido como Menla Töndrup. Mantuvo la simplicidad y amplitud de la escuela Kadam aunque poniendo gran énfasis en abundantes detalles, como resultado de la influencia persa.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>School van Tibetaanse schilderkunst die ontstond in de vroege 15de eeuw met de persoon van Menla Töndrup. De eenvoud en ruimheid van de Kadam-school bleef behouden, maar rijke detaillering kreeg meer aandacht als gevolg van Perzische invloeden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指源自十五世紀早期的西藏畫派，因此畫派畫家門拉頓珠（Menla Töndrup）而聞名。門塘派雖仍保有噶當派的簡潔與空間風格，但同時也受到波斯的影響，而更加強調豐富的細節。
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
